The Refectory is a long, austere hall where the community takes its meals in silence while one brother reads aloud from the lectern. Two rows of trestle tables stretch the length of the room, their surfaces scrubbed clean. High windows along a wall admit pale moonlight that barely reaches the stone floor. The smell of pottage lingers faintly in the air. A doorway to the south leads to the Kitchen, and wide openings to the north return to the Cloister.

> X TABLES
The tables are bare and well-washed.

