FitzAlan Crypt
A small vaulted chamber, no more than ten feet across. The central tomb bears the effigy of a knight. Flanking this is a smaller undecorated tomb. 

The walls here are finished stone rather than rough-hewn rock, and a narrow recess have been cut into them---likely once holding offerings or relics. The air is still, undisturbed for decades or longer. A patina of dust covers everything, unmarred by footprints save your own.

Against the southern wall hangs a faded wooden panel depicting an art scene, its Latin inscription barely legible in the gloom.

> * FitzAlan crypt
[Comment recorded]

