Undercroft
Barrels crowd this vaulted space beneath the Refectory. Everything the priory needs to survive is here: tallow, salt, wine, mustard, grain. A table is against a wall. The cellarer's careful hand is evident in the organisation---each item labelled, stacked, accounted for.

As cellarer, Brother Hugh alone manages this space: organising the stores, counting what remains, arranging what must be purchased. No other brother would have reason to come here uninvited.

Stairs lead up to the Kitchen. A wide door to the east allows barrels to be rolled in and out for deliveries.

