> SOUTH

Refectory
The Refectory is a long, austere hall where the community takes its meals in silence while one brother reads aloud from the lectern. Two rows of trestle tables stretch the length of the room, their surfaces scrubbed clean. High windows along a wall admit bright afternoon light that barely reaches the stone floor. The smell of pottage lingers faintly in the air. A doorway to the south leads to the Kitchen, and wide openings to the north return to the Cloister.

> WAIT UNTIL 3
Time passes.

"RING! RING! RING! RING! RING! RING!" You hear the bell ring six times to call the Brothers to the None office. You've been excused from this office, but you know the choir monks will be in the Quire for the next forty-five minutes or so.

(stopped waiting since a service is starting)
"RING! RING! RING! RING! RING! RING! RING!" You hear the bell ring seven times to call the Brothers to the Vespers office. You've been excused from this office, but you know the choir monks will be in the Quire for the next forty-five minutes or so.

> SOUTH

Kitchen
A large room, lit by high windows. A door leads north to the Refectory, and stairs descend outh to the Undercroft below. 

A large working table dominates the centre, scattered with implements and vessels. A hearth is built into the east wall, its fire warming the room.

Brother Martin is here, chopping vegetables.

Brother Remigio is here, tidying the table.

Brother Hugh arrives from downstairs.
Brother Martin heads north.

Brother Hugh heads north.

> LIGHT CANDLE
You light the beeswax candle using the hearth.

> DOWN
Brother Remigio looks away slyly as you head down the stairs.

Undercroft
Barrels crowd this vaulted space beneath the Refectory. Everything the priory needs to survive is here: tallow, salt, wine, mustard, grain. A table is against a wall. The cellarer's careful hand is evident in the organisation---each item labelled, stacked, accounted for.

Stairs lead up to the Kitchen. A wide door to the east allows barrels to be rolled in and out for deliveries.

> WAIT UNTIL 4
Time passes.

Above, you can hear Brothers Martin and Remigio talking.

Brother Hugh catches you here. "You!" he snarls, "What are you doing here?" Searching you, he finds the mustard-yellow package. "So, Brother Novice," he says quietly, his voice cold. "You've been meddling where you shouldn't."

You feel a hard object smash against the back of your head. You fall to the ground, gasping. 

You feel yourself being stuffed into an empty barrel, and can hear him hammering the lid shut. You pass out---perhaps mercifully---so you don't feel yourself being rolled off the cliffs and into the dark sea.

  *** You have died ***

